begin_memory_text: We talked about coronavirus and being in quarantine and how that has affected our lives in the past year. I mentioned being in college and looking for a job and she mentioned her job.
middle_memory_text: We talked about several things such as musical instruments, how I play guitar and she tried to learn piano at one point. We talked about our living situations, me living with my family and her living with her boyfriend. We talked about pets, I have two dogs and she wants a pet but can't get one due to her living situation.
end_memory_text: We talked about prolific and other similar websites out there. I mentioned doing an online mock trial. We talked about previous people we met through this study, how I met someone who was staying in panama and she mentioned how she went to panama on a sketchy boat one time.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going pretty average to a bit above average. I feel good right now because I have things planned and I cleaned up my room. I'm hoping to hear good news on my job search and have an interview today. So I am hopeful that things will go well.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is that we both were engaged in keeping the conversation going. Sometimes talking to people I feel unsure whether they want to keep talking or not and I drop the conversation. Knowing that we each planned to talk for 25 min made it so we both were engaged in continuing to talk for that long. It also worked well because she was a kind and friendly person who was easy to talk to.
critical_negative: I guess one thing that didn't work as well is we didn't find as much personal common ground or interest to talk about. Our conversation was about more general things like covid, travel, family, and pets. Obviously there's nothing wrong with that but I don't consider myself a very outgoing person and so the interactions I've had that lead to more long term friendships we had a lot of more specific things in common to talk about like video games and anime and music. They were very nice just that if I had to pick out something that didn't work as well it'd be that the conversation mainly stuck to getting to know you type of questions but that's not a bad thing, I think that's expected for a short conversation with someone you just met.

begin_memory_text: he graduated from college at the begining of the year, then covid happened
middle_memory_text: he lives with family, his gf went to LA, he has a job interview later and companies are scamming people
end_memory_text: his dog, his brother has an emotional support dog, and how much we both love prolific and these chats
rest_of_day_open: i see the rest of my week going well. i plan to make plans with a many people as possible. i have a bunch of free time so i plan to do whatever i want... and i want to be artsy and express myself through art and photography. and possibly bike rides at the beach
critical_positive: the fact that we allowed each other time to speak worked well. i am fully aware of the fact that i tend to cut people off which is embarrassing but i didnt do it too much to him. it happened and i didnt give him the time back to complete his thoughts
critical_negative: Had we had to talk for longer periods of time, i think it wouldve gotten boring . We would not have ran out of things to talk about because i can ask anyone a ton of questions. i just dont think we were on the same level. He seemed a bit younger and i enjoy older folk. Not saying i didnt enjoy our conversation. i did.
